  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0d82\u0da0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9a \u0db1\u0dd3\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dc5 \u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dbd\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dba\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc1\u0d82\u0dc3\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Kudos to Switzerland for relaxing Sri Lankan travel laws",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lanka Domestic Tour Operators Association (SLAITO) has expressed its appreciation for the Swiss government's decision to relax the travel advisory against Sri Lanka after President Ranil Wickremesinghe's announcement that the state of emergency will not be extended.",
        "Mr. Nishad Wijetunga, President of the Association of Sri Lanka Domestic Tourism Operations, said that Sri Lanka is working to make Sri Lanka one of the best destinations for Swiss tourists in winter.",
        "Mr. Wijetunga pointed out that this will enable Swiss tour operators to once again promote Sri Lanka.",
        "The Swiss government has recommended its citizens to be aware of the political and social situation in Sri Lanka in view of the latest developments.",
        "\"The Swiss government has informed its citizens to refrain from political discussions including on social networks and to follow the instructions of local authorities."
      ],
